" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_10578266\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_10578266\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lrc1665702814941_2.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lrc1665702814941_2.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lrc1665702814941_2.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lrc1665702814941\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                                   \n Copy and Adapt an Existing Translation Table \n      \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">It is easier to adapt an existing table than to create a new one from scratch. An existing definition can match your particular device quite closely, if not exactly.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__context_w2098ab1b5b1_w2099ab1b5_w2100ab1\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__topic_d13829e1_d13830e1_d13831e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__p_d13832e1_d13833e1_d13834e1\">Contact the device's distributor for a list of the control characters the device uses.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__topic_d13835e1_d13836e1_d13837e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__p_d13838e1_d13839e1_d13840e1\">To copy and adapt an existing translation table:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__li_d6665e1_d6666e1_d6667e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__p_d13841e1_d13842e1_d13843e1\">Import the Uniface table definitions. Start the\n               Uniface IDE with the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/imp</span> command line switch, specifying the\n               applicable XML file: <span class=\"ph filepath\">/misc/libdvc.usys.xml</span> for device\n               translation tables or <span class=\"ph filepath\">/misc/libktt.usys.xml</span> for keyboard\n               translation tables. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">/imp d:/uniface/misc/libdvc.usys.xml</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">These files contains the USYS translation table libraries.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__li_d6668e1_d6669e1_d6670e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More Editors</span> and choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Device Tables</span> or <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Keyboard Tables</span> (depending on the type of translation table).\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__li_d6671e1_d6672e1_d6673e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you have not yet created your own translation table library, create one with at least one table and press <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__li_d6674e1_d6675e1_d6676e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__p_d13844e1_d13845e1_d13846e1\">In the editor, choose\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File</span>&gt;<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Open/New</span>, select the USYS\n               library and translation table you want to modify, and click\n               <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">The Translation Table editor is opened. For example:</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__fig_d13847e1_d13848e1_d13849e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__fig_w2101ab1b5b3b7b3b3b1b1_w2102ab1b5b3b7b3b3b1_w2103ab1b5b3b7b3b3_w2104ab1b5b3b7b3_w2105ab1b5b3b7_w2106ab1b5b3_w2107ab1b5_w2108ab1\">\n<img alt=\"Device Translation Table (libdvcUSYS/dvc:P_MSWINX)\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/definedevicetableeditor.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/definedevicetableeditor.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__li_d6677e1_d6678e1_d6679e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Duplicate the translation table:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__li_d6680e1_d6681e1_d6682e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File &gt; Duplicate</span></span>. </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__li_d6683e1_d6684e1_d6685e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Navigate to and select the library in which to create the new table.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__note_w2109ab1b5b3b9b3b3b3b1_w2110ab1b5b3b9b3b3b3_w2111ab1b5b3b9b3b3_w2112ab1b5b3b9b3_w2113ab1b5b3b9_w2114ab1b5b3_w2115ab1b5_w2116ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Do not define the table in the USYS default library. It contains the standard definitions delivered with Uniface. Tables defined in this library may be overwritten when a new release of Uniface is installed.</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__li_d6686e1_d6687e1_d6688e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Provide a name that corresponds to the output device or keyboard.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__li_d6689e1_d6690e1_d6691e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__p_d13850e1_d13851e1_d13852e1\">In the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Definition</span>, edit\n               the contents of the translation table using the appropriate syntax and mnemonics. For\n               more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tqs1665702815016.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tqs1665702815016.html\" title=\"A device translation table contains delimiters that mark the beginning and end of the table and sections within the table. Each section contains mapping definitions that define an output code sequence or character, the corresponding Uniface meta code (a function mnemonic or meta character), and optional description or comments.\">Device Translation Table Syntax</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ltj1703097709703.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ltj1703097709703.html\" title=\"Keyboard translation tables map input codes from keyboards or database to logical Uniface functions and characters.\">Keyboard Translation Table Syntax</a>. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__li_d6692e1_d6693e1_d6694e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File &gt; Compile</span></span> to compile the table.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lrc1665702814941__li_d6695e1_d6696e1_d6697e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Move the compiled definitions to a deployment archive using the Resources Manager.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/btf1665702980888.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Translation Tables</a><p>To mediate between itself and the external environment, Uniface uses translation tables. Translation tables provide input and output mappings between platform-specific device codes and Uniface functions, and between external and internal character sets. Uniface provides translation tables for the platforms it supports, but you can customize these or use them to create your own tables.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dzg1703255185600.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Guidelines for Defining Keyboard Translation Tables</a><p>When defining or adapting keyboard translation tables, there are some general guidelines you should follow.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_10578266\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_10578266\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Copy and Adapt an Existing Translation Table Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Copy and Adapt an Existing Translation Table It is easier to adapt an existing table than to create a new one from scratch. An existing definition can match your particular device quite closely, if not exactly. Contact the device's distributor for a list of the control characters the device uses. To copy and adapt an existing translation table: Import the Uniface table definitions. Start the Uniface IDE with the /imp command line switch, specifying the applicable XML file: /misc/libdvc.usys.xml for device translation tables or /misc/libktt.usys.xml for keyboard translation tables. /imp d:/uniface/misc/libdvc.usys.xml Copy These files contains the USYS translation table libraries. Click More Editors and choose Device Tables or Keyboard Tables (depending on the type of translation table). If you have not yet created your own translation table library, create one with at least one table and press OK . In the editor, choose File > Open/New , select the USYS library and translation table you want to modify, and click OK . The Translation Table editor is opened. For example: Duplicate the translation table: Choose File > Duplicate . Navigate to and select the library in which to create the new table. Note: Do not define the table in the USYS default library. It contains the standard definitions delivered with Uniface. Tables defined in this library may be overwritten when a new release of Uniface is installed. Provide a name that corresponds to the output device or keyboard. In the Definition , edit the contents of the translation table using the appropriate syntax and mnemonics. For more information, see Device Translation Table Syntax and Keyboard Translation Table Syntax . Choose File > Compile to compile the table. Move the compiled definitions to a deployment archive using the Resources Manager. Related Links Translation Tables To mediate between itself and the external environment, Uniface uses translation tables. Translation tables provide input and output mappings between platform-specific device codes and Uniface functions, and between external and internal character sets. Uniface provides translation tables for the platforms it supports, but you can customize these or use them to create your own tables. Guidelines for Defining Keyboard Translation Tables When defining or adapting keyboard translation tables, there are some general guidelines you should follow. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}